Electrophysiology records the electrical signals produced by neurons using implanted electrodes. It provides high temporal resolution (sub-millisecond) and can detect individual action potentials (spikes), making it complementary to optical approaches like calcium imaging.

== Key Variants ==
* '''Single-unit recording''' — isolating the activity of individual neurons
* '''Multi-electrode arrays''' — simultaneous recording from many neurons
* '''Local field potentials (LFP)''' — lower-frequency signals reflecting population activity
* '''EEG/ECoG''' — surface-level recordings for broader spatial coverage

== Relation to Miniscope ==
Some Miniscope variants support simultaneous electrophysiology and imaging, allowing researchers to correlate optical calcium signals with electrical recordings from the same brain region.
